Strangely enough, the Martian Republic functions as more a federation of city-states than anything resembling modern nation-states. It can probably be explained by the fact it has only recently been terraformed and as such its "nations" would more function as classical city-states with colonies than anything resembling a nation. In addition to the 32 city-states on Martian surface, they hold sovereignty over Mars' two moons and several extraplanetary territories outside of the orbit of Mars; these being research, military or mining stations in the Asteroid Belt or on the moons of Saturn and Jupiter.

Oh my, where do I begin? The Saucer Pilots are essentially a set of human beings that went through a multidimensional wormhole and then drifted in space until they managed to return to Earth. Since they were in a different dimension -- aka, ours -- they found primitive humans occupying the planet and decided to study them, as they were aware of the fact that the universe wasn't exactly teeming with life. This whole debacle led to the society being strictly about the crew of the ships and the community that surrounds them (not unlike the Quarians, though much less individualistic) to the point where their society has even undergone (presumably undercover) genetic alteration to boost dopamine levels and morale for when they undergo tasks in the ship (as morale being low could potentially spell absolute disaster for the ship and/or fleet).

This is an extremely interesting factbook that I am very much enjoying. Thanks!
